The paper deals with the problem of designing channel shortening equalizers (CSEs) for broadband communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of sparse approximation techniques, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper includes numerical experiments, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
